      class UserEntity extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • createdAt
          LocalDateTime createdAt
          The creation date of the user record. This field is set automatically when the entity is created.
        • email
          @NotBlank(message="Email cannot be empty") @Email(message="Invalid email format") @Size(max=150,message="Email cannot exceed 150 characters") String email
          The email address of the user. This field must not be blank, must be a valid email, and must be unique. The maximum length is 150 characters.
        • name
          @NotBlank(message="Name cannot be empty") @Size(max=100,message="Name cannot exceed 100 characters") String name
          The name of the user. This field must not be blank and has a maximum length of 100 characters.
        • password
          @NotBlank(message="Password cannot be empty") @Size(min=8,message="Password must be at least 8 characters long") String password
          The password of the user. This field must not be blank and must have a minimum length of 8 characters.
        • phoneNumber
          @Size(max=15,message="Phone number cannot exceed 15 characters") String phoneNumber
          The phone number of the user. This field has a maximum length of 15 characters and must be unique.
        • profileImageUrl
          String profileImageUrl
          The URL of the user's profile image. This field is optional and can be null.
        • role
          Role role
          The role assigned to the user. The role defines the permissions the user has within the application.
        • userId
          UUID userId
          The unique identifier for the user. This field is the primary key and is automatically generated as a UUID.
        • version
          Long version
          The version number of the user entity. This field is used for optimistic locking to handle concurrent updates.
